Job Summary

Our client in banking industry,  is seeking for an experienced Project/Product Manager to lead end-to-end delivery of digital projects.
Mandatory Skill-set

  Bachelor of Computing/Computer Science/Information technology or equivalent;
  At least 3+ years of relevant working experience;
  Have a strong IT background;
  Experienced in end-to-end project management;
  Participated and managed different phases of project lifecycle such as business analysis, requirements gathering, testing, implementation;
  Possesses excellent interpersonal communication and analytical skills;
  A fast-learner with a passion in picking up new domain knowledge;
  Ability to work under pressure with accuracy and commitment;
  Able to work well with stakeholders such as product teams, operation teams, technology teams, partners and merchants;
  An independent and  meticulous out-of-the-box thinker who works well in teams.

Desired Skill-set

  Experience in banking industry.

Responsibilities

  Responsible for the overall digital project management from initiation to delivery of product;
  Be the point of contact for clients reporting to the Head of project delivery;
  Work closely with business stakeholders, channel, product teams, partners and merchants;
  Responsible for gathering and analyzing Business requirements and document into user Stories;
  Work closely with UX design team to conceptualize and optimize customer journey;
  Analyse and review Functional Specifications Document (FSD);
  Work in close association with a team of User Acceptance Test (UAT) Engineers;
  Collaborate with other Business Units and IT partners in identifying enhancements and ensuring end-to-end system and process delivery;
  Support post-implementation tasks and ensure customer issues are resolved within the Service Level Agreement and prompt follow-up to ensure closure of issues.

Should you be interested in this career opportunity, please send in your updated resume to apply@sciente.com at the earliest. 

